&lt;P&gt;&lt;BR&gt;The statement makes perfect sense, when you consider the servers in general.&amp;nbsp; The request is to make these two classes global, no longer tied to an expansion, in order to fulfill one of the "mission statements" of this server : for everyone to start on an equal footing.&amp;nbsp; If they are made global, however, it would apply to all servers, not just the Progression Server.&amp;nbsp; Also, if someone does not have Luclin then when Luclin is unlocked on the Progression Server, they won't be able to access the moon, but will be able to access 'content' from Luclin : tradeable spells, and gear.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;And yes, it could be done, &lt;EM&gt;&lt;U&gt;IF&lt;/U&gt;&lt;/EM&gt; they chose to.&amp;nbsp; The arguments for it are putting these two classes on an equal footing with everyone else : playable at start, the vast majority of players (&amp;gt; 99%) on other servers have these two expansions and so wouldn't be affected by making them global, and there would be just as much work with recoding mobs and mob drops in making them availalbe from day one as there would be in preventing class specific drops from those two classes from dropping before those two classes are unlocked.&amp;nbsp; So no, I don't have to accept their decision on this issue - it wouldn't be the first decision they've rethought and changed their minds on, y'know.&lt;/P&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Oh, and to the person who posted after Ermentraud, who I didn't quote : Berserkers came out with the Gates of Discord expansion, not Omens of War.&lt;/P&gt;</description>
